---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Window Replacement Endeavour Hills | Aluminium, Timber, Double-Glaze | (03) 9003 0108"
  description="Window and sliding-door replacement in Endeavour Hills 3802 — 70s–90s aluminium and steel-frame swap-outs, double-glaze upgrades for the cool foothills winters, sliding-door upgrades."
  canonical="https://berwickwindowreplacement.com.au/endeavour-hills/">

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Endeavour Hills 3802</span>
      <h1>Window replacement in <span class="accent">Endeavour Hills</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Endeavour Hills was one of the first big planned satellite suburbs
        in south-east Melbourne &mdash; built out fast through the late
        1970s and 80s, with most original window stock now 35&ndash;45 years
        old. Aluminium frames with chalky white powder coat, steel-frame
        casements at the corners of older homes, single glazing throughout,
        and condensation problems all winter long.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book a free measure</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Why Endeavour Hills</span>
      <h2>The Endeavour Hills window story.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>Late-70s and 80s stock at end of life.</h3>
        <p>
          The original Endeavour Hills estate was built out in two big
          waves from 1976 onwards. The window stock from that build is
          past 40 years &mdash; powder coat oxidised, rubber gaskets
          turned to chalk, friction stays seized, and corner-rust on the
          steel-frame windows that were also common in the era. Almost
          every job here is a full house re-window, not a single-window
          swap, because once you start pulling one out the surrounding
          ones are obviously next.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Cool-foothills winters &mdash; condensation everywhere.</h3>
        <p>
          Endeavour Hills sits at the base of the Dandenongs and gets a
          few degrees colder than the flat Casey suburbs &mdash; cool air
          drains off the hills overnight. The result is some of the
          worst single-glaze condensation in the City of Casey: water
          running off the glass onto the architraves, mould on the
          reveals in every wet room. Double-glazing is genuinely
          transformative here, not just a marketing line &mdash;
          we&rsquo;ve had owners message us after the first winter to
          say their gas heating bill dropped by a third.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Frame condensation &amp; mould remediation.</h3>
        <p>
          Roughly half the Endeavour Hills jobs we quote have visible
          mould or water damage on the timber reveals around the
          existing windows &mdash; that&rsquo;s decades of condensation
          tracking down and soaking in. We replace the affected reveals
          and architraves at the same time as the windows; trying to
          paint over wet rot is a waste. Allow $80&ndash;$200 per opening
          for reveal replacement on top of the window cost.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Typical Endeavour Hills jobs.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Full-house re-window, single-glaze, 12&ndash;15 windows ($13K&ndash;$18K)</li>
          <li>Full-house re-window with double-glaze upgrade ($17K&ndash;$23K)</li>
          <li>Add $1K&ndash;$3K for reveal &amp; architrave repair where rot found</li>
          <li>Steel-frame casement removal + aluminium replacement ($700&ndash;$1,400/window)</li>
          <li>Rear sliding-door replacement 2.4m ($2.5K&ndash;$4K)</li>
          <li>Energy-efficiency package: double-glaze + insulated reveals across 4 worst openings ($4K&ndash;$7K)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Other service areas.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/berwick/">Berwick</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/cranbourne/">Cranbourne</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/narre-warren/">Narre Warren</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/hampton-park/">Hampton Park</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/city-of-casey/">All City of Casey</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free Endeavour Hills window measure-up.</h2>
        <p>Original-build re-window jobs, double-glaze upgrades, reveal-rot repair where needed.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
